<paragraph blockId="4.[159,762,1285,1949]" lastBlockId="4.[826,1429,311,511]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">
Diagnosis (female, 
<collectingCountry box="[429,572,1784,1808]" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
individuals) — Length 284 – 304 µm. With frontal spine. Dorsal plates uniformly foveate. Genital sclerites with two and three acetabula, genital area with five pairs of perigenital setae. Telofemora 
<collectionCode box="[523,550,1925,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">III</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[616,644,1925,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">IV</collectionCode>
with 2/0 dorsal/ventral setae. Ventral flank of genu I on one leg with spur and seta, on other leg with two spurs; each ventral flank of tibiae 
<collectionCode box="[1231,1249,381,404]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">II</collectionCode>
to 
<collectionCode box="[1288,1316,381,404]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">IV</collectionCode>
with one smooth and two pectinate setae, tarsi 
<collectionCode box="[1286,1313,416,439]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">III</collectionCode>
with 4/1 dorsal/ventral setae, and tarsi 
<collectionCode box="[1206,1234,452,475]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">IV</collectionCode>
with 3/1 setae. Length of deutonymphs 234 – 244 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[826,1429,538,702]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">
Remarks — In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Romijn and Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[1054,1288,538,562]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Lobohalacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weberi">
<emphasis box="[1054,1288,538,562]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">Lobohalacarus weberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general, character states are known to vary in individuals from different localities but also within a population (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch I." box="[934,1101,643,667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80" pagination="73 - 87" refId="ref7363" refString="Bartsch I. 2007 b - Freshwater Halacaridae (Acari) from New Zealand rivers and lakes, with notes on character variability. - Mitt. hamb. zool. Mus. Inst., 104: 73 - 87." type="journal article" year="2007">Bartsch 2007b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch I." box="[1114,1186,643,667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80" pagination="490 - 510" refId="ref7677" refString="Bartsch I. 2011 b - North American freshwater halacarids (Acari), literature survey and new records. - Int. J. Acarol., 37: 490 - 510." type="journal article" year="2011">2011b</bibRefCitation>
). From 
<collectingCountry box="[1286,1429,643,667]" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="80">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
only 
<specimenCount box="[885,1010,678,702]" pageId="4" pageNumber="80" type="adult">two adults</specimenCount>
were available for study.
</paragraph>
